# Running Tests

Always run tests inside Docker using the CI script:

```bash
bash ci/run-tests-docker.sh
```

This launches a `nvcr.io/nvidia/cuda:13.2.0-devel-ubuntu24.04` container with GPU access, installs dependencies via `uv`, and runs `pytest tests/ -v`. It mirrors what CI does.

Pass extra pytest args after the script:

```bash
bash ci/run-tests-docker.sh -k "test_gemm"
bash ci/run-tests-docker.sh tests/test_examples.py -v
```

Do NOT run `pytest` directly with the local `.venv` -- the sandbox blocks GPU access and results will not match CI.

## Test Files

| File | What it tests |
|------|--------------|
| `test_lexer.py` | Tokenizer (all examples) |
| `test_parser.py` | AST construction (all examples) |
| `test_analyzer.py` | Type inference / symbols (all examples) |
| `test_bytecode.py` | Bytecode backend, cubin compilation, GPU execution |
| `test_examples.py` | CLI + end-to-end example scripts on GPU |
| `test_gpu.py` | GPU architecture detection |

GPU tests in `test_bytecode.py` and `test_examples.py` are **required**, not skipped. They must pass.
